node.title: Kiwi Ko pulls clear atop leaderboard after third round at Gainbridge LPGA
node.description: The world No. 1 has a two-shot lead with one round to play.
node.content: ["Kiwi golfer Lydia Ko remains atop the leaderboard after the penultimate round at the Gainbridge LPGA event at Florida on Sunday (NZ time).", "Starting her day in a share of the lead with American Danielle Kang, Ko has pulled two shots clear with an even-par 72 to finish at 11-under overall.", "Kang shot two-over par for the day to fall back to second, with France's Celine Boutier a shot behind in third.", "More to come"]
